      <div class="msgContentFrame">You have to be patient with the iron gear.  People are already having a hard enough time paying for repairs on the bronze haubergeons most of them shouldn't even be wearing yet.  I've been bouncing back and forth between 1 and 1.5 million gil for the last couple of weeks.  I don't put a lot of effort into earning gil; I only make things to sell these days when I've just made a big shard purchase and I want to keep my reserves topped up.  If I were actually making the effort to earn gil, I'd have a lot more.  I've got over 2600 earth shards and just over 1200 wind shards set aside for the next time I sit down to rank up armorer.  7-800 of those wind shards came from ranking THM from 16 -&gt; 18 over the last couple of days while focusing on mobs that dropped them.  Armorers that have focused on that class from day one have been the ones charging top gil for everything they make because the playerbase is still ignorant about the penalties associated with wearing gear with an optimal rank way above your class rank.  And those same armorers also got in on the ground floor when shards were as cheap as we're ever likely to see them. <br /> <br />Unless you're in a huge rush to make gear you don't really need, I'd just focus on breaking even while skilling up your class right now.  You can undercut the hell out of the rich armorers and still turn a tidy profit if you want to.  It just depends on where you get your materials and shards and how patient you're willing to be.</div>
