      <div class="msgContentFrame">Gil came easy between levels 10-20. However, now that i'm in the mid 25's it's hard to make gil because all the &quot;high&quot; armor is 27+ and requires high level leather to make. I'm spending ALOT of money on mats and shards and not making any finished products to offset the cost.  <br /> <br />I would advise making +1 or +2 of the mid level stuff. Alot of ppl are figuring out the optimum level gimp and arn't going to go crazy for the Iron haub like they did for the bronze.  <br /> <br />Also, be realistic with your prices. Istory ppl trying to sell Bronze HAub NQ non-colored for 80k+.....it's not going to move at that price. Make the HQ and sell for 70k....with all the rewards from Guildleves you shouldn't have to buy any bronze and the only cost you should incur is shards and cloth. 65k of profit per synth isn't anything to brush aside. <br /> <br />however, those guys with 40mil are the ones who made all the gear first....when bronze haubs were going for 500-400k each and selling like wildfire, or when iron was going for like 700k each....99% of crafters won't be able to take advantage of the over inflation of those pieces...keep leveling and wait till next release when the next &quot;new&quot; comes out. Be there for that..<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><a href="HTTP://www.enjin.com" rel="external nofollow" title="www.enjin.com">[img]<a href="http://sigs.enjin.com/sig-ffxiv/8976_9673d96b51ba60f6.png" title="http://sigs.enjin.com/sig-ffxiv/8976_9673d96b51ba60f6.png" rel="external nofollow">http://sigs.enjin.com/sig-ffxiv/8976_9673d96b51ba60f6.png</a>[/img]</a></div></div>
