      <div class="msgContentFrame"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">EzellLangor wrote:</div><div class="orig">however, those guys with 40mil are the ones who made all the gear first....when bronze haubs were going for 500-400k each and selling like wildfire, or when iron was going for like 700k each....99% of crafters won't be able to take advantage of the over inflation of those pieces...keep leveling and wait till next release when the next &quot;new&quot; comes out. Be there for that..</div></div> <br /> <br />This. But the next &quot;new&quot; will never come out, unless we all hit cap, which there is no &quot;new&quot;. Why? Because we can never catch up with the top rankers, because they have a lot of time and because of the fatigue barrier dictate that you will always have a gap until everyone hit the cap. And because everybody doing crafting thinking they would be able to make a quick gil have in fact, a negative impact on the market as a whole. Materials will be in more demand than the final products, people are actually making a BIG loss, except for the few that are on top and take advantage of the &quot;new&quot; things. I have resigned to satisfy myself by making stuff for my LS and not worry about how much gil I have, I will be worrying about what gears I have and what I can make instead.<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><img src="http://common.zam.com/xivsigs/1807831.png" alt="Signature Image" border="0" /></div></div>
