      <div class="msgContentFrame"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">EzellLangor wrote:</div><div class="orig">Also, be realistic with your prices. Istory ppl trying to sell Bronze HAub NQ non-colored for 80k+.....it's not going to move at that price. Make the HQ and sell for 70k....with all the rewards from Guildleves you shouldn't have to buy any bronze and the only cost you should incur is shards and cloth. 65k of profit per synth isn't anything to brush aside.</div></div> <br /> <br />I don't know that I'd call it 65k profit on a 70k sale.  Bronze Haubergeons take upwards of 100 shards to make.  At 200g/shard, that's 20k in shards minimum and right now you're lucky to even find earth shards for 200g each.  It's still profit, but I think the shard cost discourages some craters, especially when it involves them using the shards to make something that no longer grants decent skill in the rank 25+ range.  And if all you can really hope to sell are the HQ versions, you're going to be offloading quite a few NQ versions along the way. <br /> <br />I saw someone on Istory about a week ago with 5-6 iron haubergeons in their bazaar for 650k each.  I sold two in two days for a total of 650k.  That paid for the shards that made them and a lot more shards on top of that.  The key for me is to make small quantities of gear to sell and undercut the market to move them ASAP.  It's not uber gil, but it keeps me afloat right now.  And after spending the weekend ranking up THM and then a bit of time on GLA, I pulled in another 1000 wind shards which will really help. <br /> <br />I agree that the time to soak massive profit is fading fast, but we can still cover our costs and then some fairly easily.</div>
