      <div class="msgContentFrame">This takes time, but go through some of the wards (takes 1-2h) to determine what's being sold.  <br /> <br />Fill the void of what is lacking. It's a simple supply-demand thing. If no one is making hand armour, make hand armour and charge for it. Don't make 20+ of them, just make a few and sell at a good profit. Vary your retainer bazar and name it appropriately. <br /> <br />It just takes common sense to determine what to make and how to make gil, and a whole lot of research. Having a good LS who level as fast as you do, will help a lot - just be sure to spread the love around when making 120-180k items.. remember where you got that soot-black buffalo leather. :) <br /> <br />(to go sideways off topic) - It still mystifies me that people pay 300-500 gil per shard. All the shard retainers are at that price on my server. I easily go through 1k earth shards per leveling session (level 26 Armorer) yet seeking in my bazar (and retainer) I have yet to run out of earth (100 gil), wind (120 gil) or fire (80 gil). <br />I suppose if people dont keep their character online 24/7 seeking, they would have to resort to splurge spending to get the shards they need.<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>FFXI: Rison of Alexander (retired) <br />FFXIV: Rison Srithuram of Palamecia <br />LS: Omnipresence [ <a href="http://omnipresencels.com" title="http://omnipresencels.com" rel="external nofollow">http://omnipresencels.com</a> ]</div></div>
